{
  "texts": [
    "PAM produces general topics at level 1 and more specialized topics at level 2, but the super-topics are too general and similar to the overall frequency distribution to provide useful information for the user.",
    "HPA produces a similar level of specialization as PAM, except that it generates slightly more specialized topics for NG20 at level 1, but not more than CT. nTSNTM shows an increasing specialization from level 1 to level 3, with more specialized topics at level 1 than PAM and HPA.",
    "However, CT outperforms all of the models by producing reasonably high specialization for level 1 that increases up to level 3.The hierarchical affinity scores of each algorithm on the NG20 and Reuters datasets are presented in Fig. 5.",
    "It can be observed that HLDA displays a higher affinity between parent topics and their children, but the overall affinity is very low, leading to a weak relationship between super-topics and sub-topics.",
    "On the other hand, HPA and PAM exhibit high affinities between parent topics and both child and non-child topics, as their super-topics are distributions over all subtopics and are thus non-specialized."
  ]
}